						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1496 (1574 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Registers the gift of lands and gold by Tiruvēṅgaḍayyaṅgār for offerings during the recitation of Vēda on the first day of the <hi rend="bold">Tiruvāymoḻi festival,</hi> in the name of Irāyar (i.e. the King). The details of the date viz. <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1496, Bhāva, Mithuna, ba. 7, Friday, Uttiraṭṭādi correspond to 1574, A.D. June 11, Friday; ·53 f.d.t. ·28</hi></p>						

						</summary>
